**Smart Enumerations in DDD C#**

Smart enumerations are a type of enumeration that provides additional functionality beyond just defining a set of named values. In DDD, smart enumerations are often used to represent domain concepts that have a specific set of allowed values.

Here's an example of how to implement smart enumerations in C#:

```csharp
public enum Color
{
    [Description("Red")]
    Red,
    [Description("Green")]
    Green,
    [Description("Blue")]
    Blue
}

public static class ColorExtensions
{
    public static string GetDescription(this Color color)
    {
        return Enum.GetValues(typeof(Color))
            .Cast<Color>()
            .FirstOrDefault(c => c == color)
            .GetDescription();
    }

    private static string GetDescription(this Enum value)
    {
        var fieldInfo = value.GetType().GetField(value.ToString());
        var attribute = (DescriptionAttribute)fieldInfo.GetCustomAttributes(typeof(DescriptionAttribute), false).FirstOrDefault();
        return attribute != null ? attribute.Description : value.ToString();
    }
}
```

